of nuclear weapons. Serber's preface vividly conveys the mingled excitement, uncertainty, and intensity felt by the Manhattan Project scientists. This edition includes an updated introduction by Pulitzer Prize-winning historian Richard Rhodes. A seminal publication on a turning point in human history, The Los Alamos Primer reveals just how much was known and how terrifyingly much was unknown midway through the Manhattan Project. No other seminar anywhere has had greater historical consequences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAtomic bombzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPhysicistsvBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a1940s.  aamerican history.  aatom bomb.  aatomic bombs.  acontroversial.  afat man.  ahiroshima.  ajapan.  ajapanese history.  alab work.  alittle boy.  alos alamos primer.  alos alamos.  amanhattan project.  anagasaki.  anuclear bomb.  anuclear weapons.  ascientific discovery.  ascientific history.  ascientists.  auntold story.  awartime.  aweapons of mass destruction.  aweapons.  aworld history.  aworld war 2.  awwii.1 aRhodes, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSerber, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520374331zCo